history.content:
We use reserve capacities to indicate which student populations get preferential treatment and for how long. Students use phase 1 units to indicate which classes are most important to them.

There are no guarantees that classes will expand/wait lists will be cleared. If any particular class is a priority for you and/or you cannot live with uncertainty, then use phase 1 units for it. Even if you use phase 1 units and end up on the wait list, you've given yourself the best chance of getting into the class possible since you will have a better WL position than someone who waits until phase 2.
Hi, I was wondering whether I needed to phase1 cs61c and cs70 for sp20 or will there be space for me to enroll in phase 2?
